   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>Subject One Hundred Fifty-seven BELIEVE IN THE HEART</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>AND CONFESS WITH THE MOUTH Scripture: Rom 10:6-10 Christ has died and resurrected Christ is the very Savior God prepared for man.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Since He has descended from heaven, there is no need for us to ascend to bring Him down.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Here it says, Who will ascend into heaven?</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>That is, to bring Christ down.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Since Christ has already died and resurrected, there is no need for man to cause Him to die again.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Thus, because Christ has already come to accomplish redemption for us, there is no need for us to ask Him to work redemption again.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>The Holy Spirit has come and is inspiring you now Christ died and resurrected, accomplished redemption and ascended into heaven.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Now the Holy Spirit is sent to inspire man so that he can believe in Christ and His resurrection.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>The Holy Spirit is inspiring you right now; He is putting the word of Christ s redemption into you.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>This word of salvation is near you, even in your mouth and in your heart.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Once you open your mouth and exercise your heart, you will receive it.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Believe in your heart and confess with your mouth Christ s redemption has been accomplished, and the Holy Spirit has sent this redemption into your heart and your mouth.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Now, if you open your heart and your mouth just a little, you will be saved.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>The heart is for believing and the mouth is for confessing.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>Believe that Christ died and was resurrected, and confess with your mouth the Lord Jesus.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>Once you believe, you are justified; once you confess, you are saved.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>Justification means to be accepted before God and salvation means to be separated before man.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>Before God we are accepted by God, and before man we have separation.</S>
   </TEXT>
